        "subtopic": "Introduction",
        "content": "• Airports Authority of India (AAI) manages 137 airports in India.\n\n• Categories: 24 International, 10 Customs, 103 Domestic, and 26 Civil Enclaves in Defence Airfields.\n\n• AAI functions under the Ministry of Civil Aviation.\n\n• AAI is responsible for development, maintenance, and upgradation of aviation infrastructure."
      },
